Package edu.csupomona.cs.cs241.prog_assgmnt_2

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    List<K,V>
    The interface List is used to structure the classes BoundedList, UnboundedList, and LinkedList.
    Stack<E>
    The Stack interface will take in a generic type E, and will hold that item in a list that follows the LIFO rule.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Calculator
    The Calculator class contains the main for this project, and will be the interface the user uses to evaluate their expressions.
    ExpressionEvaluator
    The ExpressionEvaluator will take in a string and will use two stacks, one to hold the operators and another to hold the arguments.
    Item<K extends Comparable<K>,V>
    The Item class is used to store a value of generic type V and a key of generic type K, that will be used in the subclasses of List to store information.
    LinkedList<K extends Comparable<K>,V>
    The LinkedList class is a list that holds Items by linking each Item to the next in a chain.
    ListStack<E>
    The ListStack class implements Stack, and uses a LinkedList to hold the items of the stack.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    InvalidEvaluationException
    This exception is used when an invalid expression is called in the Calculator class.
